# Setup GitHub

When the user says **setup github** (or similar: "set up github", "connect github", "github backup"), run the command `zendoc.setupBackup`.

**Never give manual git instructions** (create repo on GitHub, add remote, push, etc.). The setup is one-click: browser opens, they sign in to GitHub, done. If you cannot run the command, say: "Press Cmd+Shift+P, type 'Set up cloud backup', and press Enter. Your browser will open—sign in to GitHub and you're done."
